cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the implementation and monitoring of hybrid SDN/OSPF networks, which are primarily related to network infrastructure and communication (cs.NI). It also addresses network security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it discusses the placement of SDN nodes and backup links. The paper also touches upon information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the timing issues of measurements. Additionally, it discusses data centers (cs.DC) as it addresses network function virtualization aspects. Finally, it briefly touches upon social and information networks (cs.SI) as it discusses the traffic matrix problem.
